	<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Actually, this is not removing the shortcut icon but rather we are making it transparent icon instead of the arrow icon.&nbsp;</p>
<p>How we do it, is we need to access it on registry using <strong>regedit </strong>command on command prompt. Once we are on the registry, we need to find the following keys:</p>
<ul>
<li>HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE</li>
<li>SOFTWARE</li>
<li>Microsoft</li>
<li>Windows</li>
<li>CurrentVersion</li>
<li>Explorer</li>
<li>Shell Icons (This key is not created on default Windows 7 registry, so we need to create this manually by doing a right-click and create new key)</li>
</ul>
<p><div class='p_embed p_image_embed'>
<img alt="Regedit" height="221" src="http://getfile7.posterous.com/getfile/files.posterous.com/temp-2012-12-09/ABjmIvvtFfEaCHHFifBClgkxuIoHzDduecphBagDskhdzhCzsarfzdIJfGGI/regedit.png.scaled500.png" width="467" />
</div>
</p>
<p>Once, we have created the Shell Icons key, we need then create a new <span style="color: #800000;"><strong><em>String Value</em></strong></span> with the following <em><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Name:&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;">29</span></strong></span></em> and <span style="color: #800000;"><em><strong>Data:</strong></em>&nbsp;</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color: #800000;"><strong><em>%SystemRoot%\System32\imageres.dll,113</em></strong></span></span></p>
<p><div class='p_embed p_image_embed'>
<img alt="Regedit-string-val" height="182" src="http://getfile7.posterous.com/getfile/files.posterous.com/temp-2012-12-09/pkJpyBFnlyFysmumycJIoAxHCuBofdrtIklmcCzfAbuijwFhekIocdkgnjrm/regedit-string-val.png.scaled500.png" width="336" />
</div>
<div class='p_embed p_image_embed'>
<a href="http://getfile5.posterous.com/getfile/files.posterous.com/temp-2012-12-09/JByexvkGtsBGFvGgucIsivcwbtxkpEskFBklkzvlmFHxcgmxjolGbHwFgmwD/Capture.PNG.scaled1000.png"><img alt="Capture" height="60" src="http://getfile2.posterous.com/getfile/files.posterous.com/temp-2012-12-09/JByexvkGtsBGFvGgucIsivcwbtxkpEskFBklkzvlmFHxcgmxjolGbHwFgmwD/Capture.PNG.scaled500.png" width="500" /></a>
</div>
<div class='p_embed p_image_embed'>
<a href="http://getfile5.posterous.com/getfile/files.posterous.com/temp-2012-12-09/scffEvrBzaygJtyjkyGFJjhyzyoqtarudJzBFvtCwaFChIqqsBkdwhclElzs/regedit-shell-icons.png.scaled1000.png"><img alt="Regedit-shell-icons" height="72" src="http://getfile1.posterous.com/getfile/files.posterous.com/temp-2012-12-09/scffEvrBzaygJtyjkyGFJjhyzyoqtarudJzBFvtCwaFChIqqsBkdwhclElzs/regedit-shell-icons.png.scaled500.png" width="500" /></a>
</div>
</p>
<p><strong>Logoff </strong>your computer and then see the cleaner shortcut icons on your desktop.</p>
<p><div class='p_embed p_image_embed'>
<img alt="D2" height="525" src="http://getfile7.posterous.com/getfile/files.posterous.com/temp-2012-12-09/DrkdlqjEFDHgJhBqwoIvommfHGaEqeqisJbptolFeodddwGykJaDyalaxEze/d2.png.scaled500.png" width="300" />
</div>
</p>
<p class="note12102012"><span style="color: #800000; font-size: medium;">Note: Sometimes the shortcut icon turn black, I think problem hooking up from the icon library, not sure, maybe someone can comment why this is happening. So, another option is to create a transparent icon and hook them up as your new Data value.</span></p>]]></content:encoded>
